      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REDZERO (2) finds an easier test today third-up. Nailed late in a fast run contest with a narrow second over 1000m at Gosford. Beautifully placed here and should prove too slick for these.  KISSAVOS (1) racing well with the big weights and the tongue-tie goes on for this. Sat on the good tempo before fading to run third over 1005m at Grafton. Shapes as the main danger from the good draw. THE WAY AHEAD (4) had mixed luck this prep and will appreciate the firmer surface today. Never comfortable on the heavy (8) surface with a respectable fourth over 1000m at Nowra. Has a strong finish and will go back from the outside gate. LOVE YOU ANYWAY (7) finished runner-up at her last three outings and comes here deep into the prep. Strong through the line with a game second over 900m at Muswellbrook. Sure to be thereabouts.",
